Firbolg

Appearance

Minotaurs and other bovine humanoids fall into the Firbolg category. They are large, lumbering creatures with temperaments as varied as the weather.

Naming Convention

Firbolgs tend to have interesting names derived from modern Indian and South asian syllables, such as Pumat or Indi.

Biology

Firbolgs can vary widely in stature, from slender to as broad as a wall, and from five feet all the way up to eight feet in height. They typically sport sheep-like ears and horns derived from the physical traits of bulls or oxen, though some have no horns at all and others have been known to have ram's horns or even antlers in some cases.

Geography

Firbolgs live primarily in the Feywild, but a few have spread into the material plane and live among society or on simple homesteads, choosing to share territory in some cases with halflings, who they inexplicably get along with quite well.
